#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/path.rst:27
msgid "The path preview that shows while drawing a path. The start of the path is indicated with a white square, the preview for the path itself in black, and the red dotted lines being the control points for the current handle."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/path.rst:29
msgid "Double-click |mouseleft| on any point of the curve or press the :kbd:`Enter` key to finish drawing, or press the :kbd:`Esc` key to cancel the entire curve."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/path.rst:31
msgid "While drawing a curve, pressing the :kbd:`Ctrl` key while dragging will push the handles both ways. The :kbd:`Alt` key will create a sharp corner, and the :kbd:`Shift` key will allow you to make a handle while at the end of the curve. |mouseright| will undo the last added point."
msgstr ""

